Manchester City striker Gabriel Jesus and defender Kyle Walker have tested positive for Covid-19, the Premier League club said on on Friday. Two other City staff members have also tested positive for the novel coronavirus, and all four are self-isolating. "Everyone at the club wishes our colleagues a speedy recovery over the Christmas period ahead of their return to work, training and competition," City said in a statement https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/gabriel-jesus-kyle-walker-covid-test-63744488. City, eighth in the league table, host Newcastle United on Saturday before visiting Everton on Monday. -REUTERS